narratives.question_text: Please rate and comment on the following aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Workload
Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Organization.Comments:
comments: It would perhaps have been valuable to watch more variety of clips/excerpts/&c at the beginning of class. I loved the selection we viewed/heard during the first quarter, and though I understand the power and import of Gospel at Colonus, I missed having the variety week to week.

narratives.question_text: Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: the Instructor.Comments:
comments: Ed facilitates great discussions. Providing the space for us to go wherever our conversations led us was much appreciated.

I deeply appreciate Ed's knowledge and insight. The formal and institutional knowledge we gained is highly valuable, and it was wonderful to take a course where the instructor didn't rigidly hold you to a syllabus. He said we'd cover everything over the semester, we trusted him, and it made for a wonderfully open semester of conversation.

narratives.question_text: Please comment on: Visitors, if any
Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Your Learning.Comments:
comments: A very informative course! The presentations were excellent exercises in researching theater companies and speaking in front of others. I learned a lot about the various stakeholders in performing arts non-profits that I hadn't been aware of before.
